lb|*BWhat call did Fred make?^^d|mb|d|
nt|Fred chose to make a takeout double. He would have liked to have been dealt a 4th heart for this call, but all of the other choices were flawed as well. Passing easily could be the winning action here, but Fred's hand was too strong (even opposite a passed partner) for him to seriously consider this call. The real choice was between 2NT and Double. |
pg| ***** 3 ***** |


hs|ss|nt|2NT certainly has some appeal as this call would have described Fred's hand accurately in a single bid. Fred ultimately rejected this choice due to his spade holding. Fred thought that it was unlikely that Dalthor would be able to provide much help in spades. Against 3NT East could duck the first round of spades and, unless there were 9 top tricks, that contract would fail.|
pg| ***** 4 ***** |


ls|ss|nt|Fred also reasoned that, if 3NT is the right contract, there is still a good chance that a takeout double could lead to 3NT. Double also brought some other possible final contracts into play that could not be reached after a 2NT overcall. Nothing is perfect with this hand, but Fred's judgment suggested that Double would have the best chance of success.|
