hs|sc|mb|p|mb|2N|an|Lebensohl|mb|p|mb|3C|
nt|After Wm passed as West, Dalthor bid 2NT - the Lebensohl convention. Lebensohl is one of the few conventions that we are willing to recommend without reservation (except for the standard caveat that you should discuss it thoroughly with your partner!). According to this convention, Dalthor's 2NT bid was an artificial relay to 3@C. Fred bid 3@C and awaited Dalthor's reply.|
pg| ***** 6 ***** |


mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|
nt|Fred was pleased that no reply came! Dalthor passed 3@C, which became the final contract. In Lebensohl, if Dalthor had bid 3@C on the previous round he would have been showing constructive values. The actual sequence is used to show a weaker hand with clubs.|
